Governor Abdullahi Sule of Nasarawa State has sent the list of 15 commissioner-nominees to the state House of Assembly for screening and confirmation as members of the state executive council. Ibrahim Balarabe Abdullahi, speaker of the House announced this after the majority leader of the house, Alhaji Tanko Tunga (APC-Awe North) submitted the list on behalf of the governor. “The 15 commissioner-nominees are, Ahmed Baba Yahaya (Toto LGA) Philip Dada (Karu LGA), Othman Bala Adam (Keffi LGA), Dr Abdulkarim Abubakar Kana (Kokona LGA), Obadiah Boyi (Akwanga LGA) Yusuf Aliyu Turaki (Awe LGA) and Dr Salihu Ahmad Alizaga (Nassarawa Eggon LGA). OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY “Others are: Dogo Shammah (Wamba LGA), Prof. Otaki Allahnanah (Keana LGA), Haruna Ogbole Adamu (Obi LGA), Ibrahim Musa Ekye (Doma LGA), Mrs Fati Jimeta Sabo (Nasarawa LGA), Abubakar Muhammed Imam (Lafia LGA), Hajiya Halima Ahmadu Jabiru (Lafia LGA) and Mohammed Bashir Aliyu (Lafia LGA),” he said. Speaker Ibrahim Balarabe directed the nominees to submit 30 copies of their curriculum Vitae (CV) on or before Friday, October 18. “The house will commence their screening from Monday October 21 to Tuesday October 22,” he added. “Those that will appear for screening on Monday, Oct 21st are commissioner-nominees from Toto, Karu, Keffi, Kokona, Akwanga, Awe, Nassarawa Eggon, Wamba and Keana “Those that will appear for screening on Tuesday, Oct 22nd are commissioner-nominees from Obi, Doma and Nasarawa and the three nominees from Lafia Local Government,” he said. Gov Sule submits list of 15 commissioner nominees to Nasarawa assembly Niger Assembly screens 7 more nominees Almakura to change commissioners few months to handover